## Alice Project — Features

### Core (Phase 0-1) ✅ Done
- [x] Pydantic config system (.env-based settings)
- [x] Alice persona definition (persona.yaml)
- [x] SQLite memory (sessions, messages, preferences)
- [x] LLM provider system (Groq + Ollama, pluggable)
- [x] Brain engine (streaming + non-streaming responses)
- [x] Dynamic context builder (system prompt + history + preferences)
- [x] Terminal chat loop (Phase 1 deliverable)

### Tool System (Phase 2) ✅ Done
- [x] BaseTool with permission model
- [x] system_info tool (time, stats, storage)
- [x] pc_control tool (open/close apps, volume, brightness)
- [x] file_ops tool (read, list, search, delete)
- [x] weather tool (OpenWeatherMap API)
- [x] news tool (RSS: world + Philippines local)
- [x] music tool (play audio file via default player)
- [x] apps tool (preset app launcher, side-by-side layout)

### Voice Input (Phase 3) ✅ Done
- [x] Mic capture loop (sounddevice)
- [x] Voice Activity Detection (amplitude-based custom VAD)
- [x] Wake word detection: "hey_alice" (OpenWakeWord, MIT)
- [x] Double clap detection (amplitude spike analysis)
- [x] STT transcription (Faster-Whisper, local)

### Custom Wake Word (Phase 3.5) ✅ Done
- [x] Synthetic training data generation (Edge-TTS, 6 voices × variations)
- [x] OWW embedding extraction + scikit-learn MLPClassifier training
- [x] ONNX export via skl2onnx

### Voice Output (Phase 4) ✅ Done
- [x] Edge-TTS integration (EN: AriaNeural, JA: NanamiNeural)
- [x] Audio playback (Windows cmd/sounddevice fallback)

### Speaker Verification (Phase 5) ✅ Done
- [x] Voice enrollment wizard (record 5 samples, scripts/enroll_voice.py)
- [x] ECAPA-TDNN embedding extraction (SpeechBrain)
- [x] Cosine similarity comparison at runtime
- [x] Accept Chester / silent reject others

### Desktop UI (Phase 6) ✅ Done
- [x] aiohttp server (HTTP + WebSocket, localhost:8765)
- [x] Chat log with real-time streaming tokens
- [x] Canvas orb visualization (idle/listening/thinking/speaking/error states)
- [x] Status indicator (header dot + label)
- [x] Settings panel (config info, toggle rows)
- [x] WebSocket bridge (Python brain ↔ browser JS)
- [x] System tray icon (pystray, purple circle)
- [x] /api/config REST endpoint
- [x] --ui flag in main.py, --ui --chat for text-only UI

### Trigger Sequences (Phase 7) ✅ Done
- [x] Double clap → Iron Man boot:
  - Play AC/DC Shoot To Thrill (if SHOOT_TO_THRILL_PATH configured)
  - Launch preset apps + tile side-by-side
  - Weather briefing (if OPENWEATHER_API_KEY configured)
  - Top 3 BBC world news headlines (voice)
- [x] Wake word → quiet start (apps + time-aware greeting, no music)
- [x] Global keyboard hotkey (Ctrl+Shift+A) → wake sequence
- [ ] Natural conversation trigger ("what do you think, Alice?") — deferred

### Bilingual EN/JA (Phase 8) ✅ Done
- [x] Auto-detect language from user input (Unicode Japanese char detection)
- [x] Manual toggle: /ja, /en commands in chat
- [x] Manual toggle: EN/JA button in UI header (broadcasts set_language WS message)
- [x] LLM responds in Japanese + appends [EN: ...] subtitle when in JA mode
- [x] Edge-TTS NanamiNeural for Japanese, AriaNeural for English (already in Phase 4)
- [x] UI parses [EN: ...] → styled subtitle block below Japanese text
- [x] language_changed WS event — UI toggle syncs on connect
- [x] DEFAULT_LANGUAGE + STT_MODEL_SIZE_JA in config + .env.example
- [x] Note: JA voice input requires STT_MODEL_SIZE=small (multilingual Whisper)

### Memory & Learning (Phase 9) ✅ Done
- [x] /remember <thing> — saves raw statement as preference (permanent, cross-session)
- [x] /forget <keyword> — removes matching preferences by keyword search
- [x] /memories — lists all saved preferences
- [x] Auto-extract preferences from conversation (keyword trigger → async LLM extraction)
- [x] usage_events table: tracks tool calls + app launches by hour/day-of-week
- [x] Proactive suggestion: injected into system prompt when pattern ≥ 3 occurrences
- [x] Tool call logging in engine (fire-and-forget asyncio.create_task)
- [x] Dynamic preference injection into system prompt (was already in context.py, now enhanced)

### UI Redesign ✅ Done
- [x] Two-panel layout: chat (60% left) + 3D sphere (40% right)
- [x] 3D wireframe constellation sphere: 96 Fibonacci nodes, ~220 edges, perspective projection
- [x] Sphere state colors: idle=cyan, listening=green, thinking=purple, speaking=amber, error=red
- [x] Message bubbles: sender label (Alice / You) + HH:MM timestamp
- [x] Cyan accent theme (replaces purple for Alice elements)
- [x] All JS APIs preserved: VoiceOrb.setState, Chat.*, WS.* — no logic changes

### Polish & Hardening (Phase 10) ✅ Done
- [x] Startup health check (python version, packages, API key, DB, voice, optional features)
- [x] Rotating log files (logs/alice.log, 5MB × 3 backups, UTF-8, suppresses noisy libs)
- [x] Windows auto-start via Task Scheduler (scripts/autostart.py install/uninstall/status)
- [x] Graceful LLM error handling (401/429/ConnectError/Timeout → user-friendly messages)
- [x] Engine error boundary (RuntimeError → surface to user, Exception → generic fallback)
- [x] --no-check flag to skip health check at startup
- [x] Full README documentation (all phases, troubleshooting, architecture, tech stack)
